Summary

Biked a lot, got nothing done programming wise, amazing week. I'm moving this week, I'll have more time for side project stuff once I'll be settled.

Cycling

Biked 139 km last week, and went up a total of 1171m. At the beginning of the week, I was really afraid to go downhill, my back wheel vibrated a lot. Turns out my wheel isn't true and at high speed it vibrates a bit, once I knew this, the next times I went downhill, I didn't panic when I felt the wheel vibrate and I could really enjoy the ride. Going downhill on a bike is an amazing experience, the feeling of speed at 60 km/h is just something else. I really love the idea of suffering going up the hill in order to earn the downhill.
